Klopp:  &quot;First and foremost, I have to say big congratulations to Senegal on the achievement of qualifying for the World Cup; this is fantastic news for their country and the players - Sadio included.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;Personally speaking, I&rsquo;m delighted for Sadio. Everyone in Liverpool knows his ability and the best players should be on the best stage - Sadio will now have this wonderful chance.&quot;

Klopp on Man&eacute;: &quot;Specifically on him returning to Melwood early to be with us; obviously it is a concern that the hamstring injury is again on the agenda and it will be critical for us to monitor and manage that in the coming days.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;At this stage we haven&rsquo;t seen Sadio yet to properly assess the extent, but what is clear is that we will have to stay on top of this for the rest of the week and make sure we are careful in how we look after him.&quot;

Klopp: &quot;It should not be forgotten in Liverpool, either, how important it is to Sadio that he represents his country whenever he is fit enough to do so. He is so proud of his country and recognises what a role model he is for them.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp on Man&eacute;: &quot;In this moment all I can really say with certainty is that we will assess Sadio as soon as he lands back in the country &amp; make decisions on what rehab and treatment gives him the best chance of being back fit and strong for the important fixtures we have coming.&quot;
